title: [Olbin Pass, South Rim]
description: A rugged butte forms the southern edge of the pass.   Below it, a concave bowl sweeps down towards the tree line, its curved depression filled with snow.  Wandering through the forest beyond, a twisting trail can be seen leisurely making its way down the mountain.  To the east and west, tall peaks cradle the pass.
paths: Obvious paths: north, northeast, east, northwest
